Populations may show localised specificity. It is widespread across northern Australia. |
| Selenothrips rubrocinctus      | Red banded cacao thrips          | Mainly feeds on mature leaves of many tree species including mango, avocado, cacao, and a large number of ornamental and shade trees. It is widespread in Australia, reported in NSW, NT, Qld, SA and WA. |
| Stenchaetothrips biformis      | Rice thrips                      | Various Poaceae, normally in damp places. It is present in NSW and Qld. |
| Thrips florum                  | Oriental flower thrips           | Feeds and breeds in a large number of flowering plants, but is only sometimes considered to be a pest. It has been recorded from plants in the families Ericaceae, Rosaceae, Rubiaceae, Rutaceae and Verbenaceae. It has been mainly recorded in Qld, but sometimes in NSW, NT and WA.